data.title: Alfred Nobel and His Prizes From Dynamite To DNA
data.meta_description:
Alfred_Nobel_and_His_Prizes_From_Dynamite_to_DNA - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. 1) Alfred Nobel was a Swedish chemist, engineer, and inventor who left the majority of his fortune to establish the Nobel Prizes upon his death in 1896. 
2) The prizes were first awarded in 1901 and are given annually for achievements in physics, chemistry, physiology or medicine, literature, and peace.
3) This article discusses Alfred Nobel's background and inventions, the establishment of the Nobel Foundation and prizes, and provides commentary on the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine.
